    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="415"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Argentina/9–745:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-07T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 7, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1231. Paragraph C 3 of Oilseeds-Fuel Oil agreement provides “The Argentine
                    Government hereby undertakes to facilitate by all the means in its power the
                    consummation of the purchases at the prices herein named and particularly the
                    availability of the products”, etc. After consultation with FEA officials, it
                    was revealed Argentine Government officials had agreed with Butler, FEA
                    representative, if necessary, to (1) give highest railroad priorities for these
                    commodities, (2) set ceiling prices at levels to permit movement of seeds to
                    crushers and peanuts for export and further affirmed to take action as indicated
                    in Embs 1620 of July 23.<note n="91" xml:id="d415fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    Argentina should be asked to take these and any other necessary measures, such
                    as inventory controls, to make available for export quantities not reasonably
                    needed for current domestic consumption and not required for normal export
                    quotas for other American Republics.</p>
                <p>Since urtel 2024 of Aug 30<note n="91" xml:id="d415fn2">Not printed.</note>
                    indicates that present Argentine officials are not implementing agreement as to
                    edible oils and in view of recent changes in personnel handling matter, FEA and
                    Dept suggest that Emb assisted by FEA representative explore and confer anew
                    with appropriate Argentine officials need for Argentine Govt carrying out the
                    responsibility it undertook in signing the Agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
